cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SD 

This paper focuses on improving Recurrent Neural Networks (RNNs) for sequence labeling tasks, which are commonly studied in the field of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper proposes new variants of RNNs, which involve modifications to the architecture and training process, indicating a potential fit for the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also evaluates the performance of the models on different datasets, suggesting a possible fit for the sub-categories of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SD (Software Engineering).
